Algorithm description: The new algorithm assigns scores to each bin based on the sum of the logarithm of the reciprocal of the rest capacities of each bin, the difference between the maximum capacity and the item size, and the product of the reciprocal of the sum of the rest capacities.

Code:

import numpy as np

def score(item: int, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:
    num_bins = len(bins)
    
    # Calculate the sum of the logarithm of the reciprocal of the rest capacities of each bin
    sum_log_reciprocal_rest_capacities = np.sum(np.log(1 / bins))
    
    # Calculate the difference between the maximum capacity and the item size
    diff_max_item = np.max(bins) - item
    
    # Calculate the reciprocal of the sum of the rest capacities
    reciprocal_sum_rest_capacities = 1 / np.sum(bins)
    
    # Calculate the scores based on the modified formula
    scores = sum_log_reciprocal_rest_capacities + diff_max_item + reciprocal_sum_rest_capacities
    
    return scores
